0	//! Merge Barrier determines which files have modifications during the merge operation
1	//!
2	//! For every unique path in the input stream, a barrier is established. If any
3	//! single record for a file contains any delete, update, or insert operations
4	//! then the barrier for the file is opened and can be sent downstream.
5	//! To determine if a file contains zero changes, the input stream is
6	//! exhausted. Afterwards, records are then dropped.
7	//!
8	//! Bookkeeping is maintained to determine which files have modifications, so
9	//! they can be removed from the delta log.
10	
